<br>
I get on the boards and say that I just found out I got cancer/aids/lupus/whatever. <br>
<br>
People are sad and donate money to their local charities to fight cancer/aids/lupus/whatever.<br>
<br>
I don't really have cancer/aids/lupus/whatever. <br>
<br>
I realize this is just a large case of 'end justifying means', but how evil is it? I was thinking about the thread about what PoSarhea feels strongly about and I was thinking that people need to give to more charities.<br>
<br>
And then I was thinking about how much I would be giving if I had a disease, and all my RL friends. Then I thought on here, about how on the internet you could say you were a 14 year old boy or a 67 year old grandmother and noone could REALLY tell if you are lying or not.<br>
<br>
Just kinda musing things over here in the coffee talk.<br>
<br>
Please don't think any less of me.<br>
<br>
Kuladen<br>
